lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

dc:date  a      owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_703  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 4 ADAM22 binds LGl1 and regulates the number of synaptic AMPARs\n\nLiteral\n\"The effects of LGI1 on synaptic currents could be prevented by preincubation of LGI1 with ADAM22-ED (Fig. 4A) (ADAM22-ED 0 0.59 T 0.06; LGI1þADAM22-ED 0 0.65 T 0.07), suggesting that an interaction between LGI1 and ADAM22 was required for the increased AMPA/NMDA ratio. To determine whether LGI1 directly affects the number of synaptic AMPARs, we measured AMPAR-mediated spontaneous miniature excitatory postsynaptic currents (mEPSCs). LGI1 incubation increased the average amplitude of these events (n 0 17, both groups, P G 0.005), and preincubation of LGI1 with ADAM22-ED blocked this increase (Fig. 4, B and D).\"\n\n7/6/2017 Pim\n- The role of ADAM22 in this process is derived form combined evidences:\n(i) ADAM22 is a receptor for LGI1 in neurons (Fig.3). Literal: \" Taken together, these results imply that secreted LGI1 serves as a specific extracellular ligand for ADAM22 and that the LGI1/ADAM22 complex is scaffolded by PSD-95.\"\n(ii) ADAM22-ECD infusion acts as a dom.neg. for the activation of postsynaptic ADAM22 receptors by LGI1 (Fig.4) that mediates the increase of synaptic AMPA receptors.. Experimental description: Information form Supporting Online Material\n\n\"Acute hippocampal slices (300-400 μm) were obtained from P24-P29 Sprague-Dawley rats with standard procedures.\"\n\n7/6/2017 Pim\n- Species of the infused Adam22 protein is unknown. Species information requested to Masaki Fukata (mfukata@nips.ac.jp , d.d. 7/6/2017). His answer was:\n\"Dear Dr. Pim van Nierop,\n\nThank you for the note.\n\nIn the paper, we used the following genes.\n\nADAM22 is \"mouse\".\nLGI1 is \"rat\".\n\nBest regards,\nMasaki\"\n\nThe species was set to **mouse** based on this reply." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_703" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

